title: Looming Oil-Supply Shock Launches Debate in OPEC
description: The prospect of a European embargo and a price cap on Russian oil, along with rising winter demand, are weighing on the production group.

title: Confronting Iran Protests, Regime Uses Brute Force but Secretly Appeals to Moderates
description: The unrest poses a serious challenge to the clerical regime’s rule. Purges of rivals and reformists from the government have narrowed officials’ options for a response.

title: Western Allies Aim to Agree on Russian Oil Price Cap Wednesday
description: Officials are discussing setting the price cap at around $60 a barrel, as the group rushes to finalize the plan before it begins early next month.

title: EU Unveils Proposal to Cap Natural-Gas Prices
description: The bloc’s executive arm said its proposal was designed to deal with exceptional circumstances where the benchmark price for natural gas in Europe reaches a certain threshold.

title: Iran Says It Has Stepped Up Production of Highly Enriched Uranium
description: Iranian officials said Tuesday that the country has started producing near-weapons-grade enriched uranium at a second nuclear facility in response to Tehran being formally rebuked last week for failing to cooperate with the United Nations’ atomic-energy agency.

title: Senators Urge Biden Administration to Provide Ukraine With Armed Drones
description: A bipartisan group of legislators wants the U.S. to give Ukraine Grey Eagle drones, saying the technology could help Kyiv to hold its territory.

title: Ukraine Launches Assault to Oust Russia From Key Black Sea Peninsula
description: Ukrainian forces began an assault on the Kinburn Spit, a strip of land jutting into the sea south of Mykolaiv, that has been occupied for months by Russian forces, as Kyiv looks to open up its besieged ports.

title: Kamala Harris Seeks to Strengthen Philippines Alliance Amid Fraught China Relations
description: Vice president touts the proposed expansion of a military pact and pledges $7.5 million for the country’s maritime law-enforcement agencies on a visit to the country.

title: A Big Winner From Qatar's World Cup: Dubai
description: While its neighbor grapples with a culture clash and the logistics of running the tournament, Dubai is awash with supporters wanting easy access to beer, cheaper accommodation and a setting more accustomed to Western tourism.

title: Russia's Munitions Shortages Raise Questions Over How Long It Can Continue Ukraine War
description: Both sides have suffered heavy losses of men and materiel, but Moscow is more dependent on its shrinking economy to replenish supplies, while Kyiv has powerful backers.

title: Indonesia Earthquake Death Toll Rises to at Least 268
description: Search-and-rescue teams continued to find bodies under wrecked buildings, a day after the 5.6-magnitude quake.

title: U.S. and Chinese Defense Chiefs Meet in Reflection of Easing Tensions
description: The meeting was the latest sign of thawing ties between the two countries after a rupture in August following a trip to Taiwan by House Speaker Nancy Pelosi.
